snippet.textDisplay: So where do we go from here? Signings needed in this Jan window but who? che Adams? No, because Ralph Hasenhüttl is scared for his job and threw his toys out of the pram when asked about Adam's services.Luke Freeman? No, because Chris Wilder has some hidden bitterness towards Leeds Utd and would like them to stay in Championship football.Any Liverpool players currently on their books? No, because Jürgen Klopp is a money-grabbing pickled cabbage muncher. Having a successful signature for a frontman is going to be damn near impossible yet again. Even signing an unproven striker will come with its hurdles. Marcelo Bielsa has continued to have faith in Patrick Bamford, despite having "options" available. It would take Patrick to pick up an unfortunate injury for any new signing to pave his way and be given game time and experience. Marcelo I believe has made a rod for his own back by signing loan players and not utilising the matchday squad enough to make any parent club believe Leeds would be a great fit for any footballers development. Leeds need a tall, physical CB,  Illan Meslier to start and even a seasoned striker so Leeds can get over the line...On a side note, Carlo Poveda looks an interesting scout though.
